            <p>N. Y. August 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5650<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am instructed by<lb/> the Trustees of Cong. Zichron<lb/> Ephraim to extend to you a<lb/> cordial invitation to deliver<lb/> the dedication of their new synagogue&#44;<lb/> in 67th St between 3rd and Lexington<lb/> Avenues&#44; which will take place<lb/> on Sunday&#44; the 7th of September&#44;<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#44; at 2 P. M.  The Trustees<lb/> feel confident that the principle<lb/> and standpoint of the congreg&#45;<lb/>&#45;ation&#44; unflinching orthodoxy<lb/> and secular culture and decorum&#44;<lb/> are such as you&#44; the veteran<lb/> and venerable champion of<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>orthodox Judaism in America&#44;<lb/> will entirely sympathize with<lb/> and hope&#44; therefore&#44; that you will<lb/> make it possible to honor them<lb/> with your presence on this import&#45;<lb/>&#45;ant occasion.  It is self under&#45;<lb/>&#45;stood that your expenses will<lb/> be refunded.  Please answer at<lb/> once as the programmes must<lb/> be printed early next week.<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping to receive an affirm&#45;<lb/>&#45;ative answer&#44; I remain with<lb/> best regards<lb/> By Order of the Board of Trustees<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/> Minister<lb/> Chairman of the Committee of Arrangements<lb/> 420 E. 50th St<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
